Nancy Wilson (jazz singer) https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nancy_Wilson_(jazz_singer) 0 Nancy Sue Wilson (born February 20, 1937) is an American singer whose career spanned over five decades, beginning in the mid–1950s until retiring in the early–2010s. Wilson has more than seventy albums and has won three Grammy Awards for her recordings. Wilson has been labeled a singer of blues, jazz, R, pop and soul, a "consummate actress", and "the complete entertainer". The title she prefers, however, is "song stylist". She has received many nicknames including "Sweet Nancy", "The Baby", "Fancy Miss Nancy" and "The Girl With the Honey-Coated Voice".
